Liverpool manager Jurgen Klopp, has described Mohamed Salah, as one of the best players in the world after the Egyptian renewed contract at the club on Friday. Klopp went on to reckon that Salah still has his best years ahead of him in his football career. Salah’s new contract will now keep at Anfield till 2025 after the 30-year-old enjoyed five stunning seasons with the Reds. He has scored 156 goals in 254 appearances, and won the Champions League, Premier League, FA Cup and League Cup. “This is a special treat for our supporters to enjoy their weekend even more,’ Klopp told Liverpoolfc.com. Klopp believes that supporters of the club will celebrate the Egyptian’s decision, saying he is “really pleased, really, really pleased. He said the 30-year-old has taken the best decision for his career and also for the club, adding that “He belongs with us I think. This is his club now.” “Mo is one of the best players in the world; it’s only normal there are things to sort when you are at his level. ‘I have no doubt Mo’s best years are still to come.”